Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, buff. Rectangular, rounded stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). Name Timarchos. From the same die as 1925,0119.144b and 554a and 2011,5003.332.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0433)
